rComments: Good lecturer, can tend to go on for long periods with tons of material in the slides. Assignments were not too difficult, but the grading was a bit tough, final exam isn't too difficult if you go over the key terms and important concepts from the readings and the book.

rComments: I've taken two courses w/ him. His lectures are good for expanding your understanding of the readings and he has his funny moments. He is also very helpful outside of class; he's helped my friends and I with our grad school applications a lot. He's very fair so if you do the work you will do well. He's also easy on the eyes.

First of all,just as a person he's very beautiful, and charming as well. Loves talking about Belgium, it's funny. the class content is very boring though, and its not him I like him but he isn't good enough to make it not be boring. Therefore unless you're passionate about public policy, I would not recommend this course. Prof is super cute though.
